While `pygame.K_f` is a key enumerator constant (see [`pygame.key`](https://www.pygame.org/docs/ref/key.html)) the content of `event.type` is event enumerator constant (see [`pygame.event`](https://www.pygame.org/docs/ref/event.html)).  
If you want to determine if a certain key is pressed, the you&#39;ve to verify if the event type is `pygame.KEYDOWN` (or `pygame.KEYUP` for button release) and if the `.key` attribute of the event is equal the key enumerator. e.g.:

```py
for event in pygame.event.get():
    if event.type == pygame.QUIT:
        self.quit()

    # [...]

    if event.type == pygame.KEYDOWN:
        if event.key == pygame.K_f:
            # [...]
```

